    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hi @kaliubuntu0206, `extendProvider` works fine for me with `eth_sendTransaction`. Adapting the code from the docs:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nconst { ProviderWrapper } = require( 'hardhat/plugins')\r\n\r\nclass LogProvider extends ProviderWrapper {\r\n  constructor(\r\n    _wrappedProvider\r\n  ) {\r\n    super(_wrappedProvider);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  async request(args) {\r\n    if (args.method === \"eth_sendTransaction\") {\r\n      console.log(\"some eth_sendTransaction\")\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return this._wrappedProvider.request(args);\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nextendProvider(async (provider, config, network) => {\r\n  const newProvider = new LogProvider(provider);\r\n  return newProvider;\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nI send some transactions and get that log.\r\n\r\nI'm tentatively closing this, but I'll re-open if you can give us more precise reproduction steps.",
